The paper deals with the throughput of multi-user MIMO networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of genetic algorithms for scheduling also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also considers interference cancellation and power amplifiers' efficiency, which are topics related to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia systems (cs.MM).
